msgstr "Solar no utilizado por horas"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:56
msgid "Share Spain’s wasted sun"
msgstr "Comparte el sol desperdiciado en España"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:65
msgid "Why pay for the same electricity twice?"
msgstr "¿Por qué pagar dos veces la misma electricidad?"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:67
msgid ""
"\n"
"    On sunny hours, the peninsula sometimes produces more solar power "
"than the grid can absorb locally.\n"
"    That energy may go unused while other plants stay in the mix—so "
"consumers can end up paying for\n"
"    flexibility and constraints twice over.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    En las horas soleadas, la península a veces produce más solar de la "
"que la red puede absorber en la zona.\n"
"    Esa energía puede quedar sin usar mientras siguen otros tipos de "
"generación: los consumidores pueden acabar pagando\n"
"    la flexibilidad y las restricciones dos veces.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:74
msgid ""
"\n"
"    <strong>What helps?</strong> Stronger grids and storage over time—and"
" market signals that reward\n"
"    using clean power when it is abundant, which can reduce waste and "
"ease bills.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    <strong>¿Qué ayuda?</strong> Redes y almacenamiento más robustos con "
"el tiempo, y señales de mercado que premien\n"
"    usar energía limpia cuando sobra, lo que puede reducir el desperdicio"
" y aliviar la factura.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:82
msgid "City-sized picture"
msgstr "A escala de ciudad"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:84
#, python-format
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Today’s unused solar total is in the ballpark of the daily "
"electricity of about\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> typical homes, using an illustrative "
"%(kwh)s kWh per home per day\n"
"    for the analogy (not a census count—see methodology).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El total de solar no utilizado hoy ronda el consumo diario de unas\n"
"    <strong>%(homes)s</strong> viviendas típicas, con un valor "
"ilustrativo de %(kwh)s kWh por hogar y día\n"
"    para la analogía (no es un censo; ver metodología).\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:93
msgid "Methodology"
msgstr "Metodología"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:95
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Quarter-hourly unused solar energy (MWh) comes from the project "
"database: each row is keyed by\n"
"    date_day with columns qh_1_mwh through qh_100_mwh (15-minute "
"buckets). Multiple rows for the same\n"
"    day are summed bucket-wise before display.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    La energía solar no utilizada por cuartos de hora (MWh) proviene de "
"la base de datos del proyecto: cada fila\n"
"    va por date_day con columnas qh_1_mwh a qh_100_mwh (intervalos de 15 "
"minutos). Si hay varias filas el mismo\n"
"    día, se suman los cubos antes de mostrarlas.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:102
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The chart aggregates those quarter-hours into 24 hourly bars "
"(Europe/Madrid calendar day). Any slots\n"
"    beyond the first 96 are folded into the last hour of the day. Day "
"totals are the sum of all\n"
"    quarter-hour values. “So far this year” uses SUM(total_mwh) across "
"rows from 1 January through the\n"
"    selected date. The headline “per hour” figure is the mean of the 24 "
"hourly bars (equivalently the\n"
"    day total divided by 24).\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    El gráfico agrega esos cuartos de hora en 24 barras horarias (día "
"natural Europa/Madrid). Los huecos\n"
"    más allá de los primeros 96 se incorporan a la última hora del día. "
"Los totales del día son la suma de\n"
"    todos los cuartos. “Lo que llevamos de año” usa SUM(total_mwh) entre "
"filas del 1 de enero hasta la fecha\n"
"    elegida. El titular “por hora” es la media de las 24 barras (equivale "
"a total del día / 24).\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:111
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Euro amounts appear only when WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH is set; they are"
" a simple illustrative rate\n"
"    times energy, not a market settlement.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Los importes en euros solo aparecen si se define "
"WASTED_SUN_EUR_PER_MWH: son un tipo ilustrativo\n"
"    por energía, no un cierre de mercado.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:116
msgid "Household analogy"
msgstr "Analogía con hogares"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:118
msgid ""
"\n"
"    The household comparison uses a configurable illustrative kWh/day "
"figure to give an intuitive\n"
"    scale; replace or calibrate it when you publish official assumptions."
"\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    La comparación con hogares usa un valor ilustrativo de kWh/día "
"configurable para dar una escala intuitiva;\n"
"    sustitúyelo o calíbralo cuando publiques supuestos oficiales.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:126
msgid "About"
msgstr "Sobre"

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:128
msgid ""
"\n"
"    Built by Enrique Tasa, Head of Technology at Octopus Energy Spain.\n"
"    "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"    Creado por Enrique Tasa, Director de Tecnología en Octopus Energy "
"España.\n"
"    "

#: wasted_sun/templates/day.html:135
msgid ""
"\n"
"  Figures are estimates for public understanding, not official Red "
"Eléctrica or government statistics.\n"
"  "
msgstr ""
"\n"
"  Las cifras son estimaciones para entender el fenómeno, no estadísticas "
"oficiales de Red Eléctrica ni del Gobierno.\n"
"  "

